column5: Can someone please tell me when musky opens on the West Arm of Nipissing.  I'm thinking the 4th Saturday in June but my old brain is getting foggy ??
Yup - Saturday June 16.   We'll be there for opening day.  Sure hope they're hungry.

gonna be different this opener , the water temps are already up to 66*.. I've heard of 8 x 50" + caught this past weekend alone, biggest being 56" at Gibraltar... all but 2 came off the reefs east of Target , Fisherman while fishing for Walleye, a 52" by the mouth of the Veuve River in Cache Bay..the rest in open water.  Should be a good opener but they probably won't be in their usual haunts.   Randy
Thanks Randy, sounds like maybe an excellent season coming up.
Gonna be a challenge for me to have a better year than last year ... but we're gonna give it the old collegr try.

Randy I also saw some big walleye caught this past weekend. Our park produced 29", 28", 26", and 25". I have a buddy that pre-fished Cache Bay this past weekend and he did terrible fishing spots he "thought" the pike would be at.
stupid question,what was your buddy "pre-fishing" for?
He was fishing for pike. Pre-fishing for a tournament that is in that area this coming weekend.
one of my buddies caught two near 40-inchers while fishing for pike this pass weekend..  the capt..
Get your fish'n pole rigged up Kevin, I'll see you in a couple weeks
give Roger's Bay a shot for me will you Lew?
I sure will bud, it's a place I never pass without at least a few casts.
And you're noting posting the coordinates of such Roger's Bay on Lake X
